<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 4:12PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Macon,
Peach, northwestern Houston, south central Crawford and east central
Taylor Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 412 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Nakomis, or 8 miles
west of Fort Valley, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Perry, Fort Valley, Warner Robins, Centerville, Byron, Marshallville,
Reynolds, Saint Louis, Nakomis, Meadowdale, Hicks, Lakewood,
Powerville, Moss Oak, Lee Pope and Miami Valley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
